    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Move with confidence.  You have the support to do it.  Strong events, strong Companions, solid weapons.  Make his Shadow beat you, don&#8217;t do it yourself by playing too conservative.  Play smart though.  This Fellowship generates ankle deep Pools.  Holding 2 SotSF, 2 Intimidate, and A Mysterious Wizard still?  Might want to move.  Already opened the sluice gates by bottoming out your hand playing Sleep and Weapons and looking at a handful of Shadow for support?  Might want to ease off the gas and build your reserves.  The Big Uruks, with the help of their boosters, put the roadblock down and punish the 5+ Fellowships.  Eviscerate the Pretty Boys with Savagery and Battle Cry.  <br />
<br />
Most powerful card?  Gandalf, Grey Haired Spark Plug.  He makes the whole thing move.  He&#8217;s the Great Manipulator, Protector, and overall Tank.  Stop wounds with him, get rid of conditions, sap a beastly Minion.  And with the other races on the table, plus Glamdring, he&#8217;s a monster.  He&#8217;s money.<br />
<br />
Supporting cast: Servant of the Secret Fire.  This card is by far, IMO, the best event in the game.  Wrecks any Minion, regardless of who&#8217;s dancing with the Big Ugly.  Save someone from getting overwhelmed or win a skirmish.  All of a sudden, the Cave Troll is feeling a bit wobbly, the Witch King is a little short, Lurtz becomes a grease stain.  Please exit stage right.  Barliman Butterbur gets the right cards back when I need them.  Intimidate is also huge.  Personal choice here, Hate is insanely popular with the group I play with, stopping that one wound, at the right time, in a key situation, can be the difference between letting Aragorn sit this one out and finishing strong with all your Crew still on the table.  Cuts down on the damage +1 wrecker, allowing someone to face one of the Nasties with impunity.  Minor mention=the Weapons.  Glamdring and Sting will cut the Twilight and the direct damage weapons can whittle down the Swarms.   <br />
